Author: ComputerGenie üë¥üèºüì¢#7004
Content: There is no staking in KMD. KMD does have a "usage reward" where you get a bonus reward for using it. Merely sending a transaction that meets certain rules allows you to earn this reward. Staking requires you to actively produce a block. These are completely different things. The user rewards don't "come from" x or y, they are created with the transaction at the time of the transaction. The amount that users get as a reward does not exist before the user gets the reward. The rewards are created by the protocol as a form of emission.
